Sentencas: Conducting ceramic layers with a spinel structure of MnCo2O4 and a thickness of 3 mu m were deposited on ferritic stainless steel (SS) by aerosol deposition (AD), for use as an oxidation-resistant coating layer on the metallic interconnects of a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Dense spinel MnCo2O4 film coating by aerosol deposition on ferritic steel alloy for protection of chromic evaporation and low-conductivity scale formation

Sentencas: The microstructural changes in the interface between the MnCo2O4 and SS were analyzed, as were the subsequent electrical conductivity changes at an SOFC operating temperature of 800 A degrees C in air.
Titulo: Dense spinel MnCo2O4 film coating by aerosol deposition on ferritic steel alloy for protection of chromic evaporation and low-conductivity scale formation

Sentencas: The coated spinel layers were dense without pores or cracks, and maintained good adhesion even after oxidation at 800 A degrees C for 1,000 h in air atmosphere.
Titulo: Dense spinel MnCo2O4 film coating by aerosol deposition on ferritic steel alloy for protection of chromic evaporation and low-conductivity scale formation

Sentencas: Close observation of the interface between the coated spinel oxide and SS substrate indicated the presence of 1-mu m thick, Cr-rich scale formation; however no MnCrCoO4 or MnCr2O4 spinel phase was detected.
Titulo: Dense spinel MnCo2O4 film coating by aerosol deposition on ferritic steel alloy for protection of chromic evaporation and low-conductivity scale formation

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) of the MnCo2O4-coated alloy after heat treatment at 800 A degrees C for 1,000 h was 13.4 m Omega cm(2).
Titulo: Dense spinel MnCo2O4 film coating by aerosol deposition on ferritic steel alloy for protection of chromic evaporation and low-conductivity scale formation
